##WHEN TO KILL1 PID / 2PID / AUTOSCLALE
**If #1 process uses 900%+ CPU** MEANS MORE THAN DOUBLE FO 400% CPU CC = Kill ONLY that 1 process (happens 90% of time)
**If Top 2 processes each use 400%+ CPU** FULL OF FOR 4 CORE MEANS EACH USE APRPX 200%+200 MEAN 2 CORE EACH = Kill entire apache2 service (happens 8% of time)  
**If ALL top 3 processes use less than 200% CPU** = Add more servers (autoscale) (happens 2% of time)

2 -- HIGH LOAD BY ZOMBIE


CPU ISSUE #2: ZOMBIE PROCESSES (High Load, Low CPU)===1           ZOMBIE SUMMERY=== 18/4 cores so 14 process pending but cpuutil 18% only so low cpu but 14 load fake --use top
1. what is Zombie = Dead child process parent forgot to clean up
Uses: 0% CPU, 64KB RAM, 1 process table slot
STAT column shows "Z" in top command 

2. Why "Load High + CPU Low" = Zombie Clue
Load Average 18.5/4 cores + CPU 18% = PARENT PROCESS WAITING
NOT zombies causing load â†’ PARENT in D state (I/O wait) trying to reap
JIRA shows: "Load 18.5 | CPUUtil 18%" â† RUN FOR ZOMBIES

3. EXACT Jira Messages (Memorize)
âœ… REAL CPU: "Load 15.2 | CPUUtil 95%"
âœ… ZOMBIES:  "Load 18.5 | CPUUtil 18%"
âœ… I/O WAIT: "Load 12.1 | Disk 95% | %wa 65%"


CPU ISSUE #2: ZOMBIE PROCESSES (High Load, Low CPU)===1           ZOMBIE SUMMERY=== 18/4 cores so 14 process pending but cpuutil 18% only so low cpu but 14 load fake --use top
Load 18.5/4 + CPUUtil 16%	     
SOLUTION ====
ps -aux| grep z              === to find zombie processes.                                            
ps aux |grep 'z'|wc -l        === Number of zombie process
kill -9 6789 â†’ Zombies vanish instantly
