CPU ISSUE #3: I/O WAIT (Disk Thrashing)
text
**JIRA INFRA-1236** âš ï¸ P1  
prod-db-01 | Load: 12.1/4 cores | Disk IOPS: 95% | %wa: 65%
CloudWatch: VolumeReadOps >5000 | MySQL slow
1. ACK PagerDuty - Tap SMS
2. SSH database - ssh ubuntu@prod-db-01
3. Check I/O - iostat -x 1 5 (%util=95%, await=45ms)
4. Find culprit - iotop -ao (mysqld 2.1GB/s reads)
5. Lower priority - renice 10 -p $(pgrep mysqld)
6. Clear caches - echo 3 > /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches
7. Monitor recovery - iostat -x 1 3 (%wa dropping)
8. Jira resolution - "âœ… MySQL I/O throttling, reniced + cache cleared"

CPU ISSUE #4: JAVA THREAD EXPLOSION
text
**JIRA INFRA-1237** ðŸš¨ P0  
prod-app-01 | Load: 8.5/4 cores | java: 450% CPU
CloudWatch: HeapUsed 95% | Tomcat threads >200
1. ACK PagerDuty - Phone call answered
2. SSH app server - ssh ubuntu@prod-app-01
3. Spot Java - top (java PID=9876, 450% CPU)
4. Thread count - ps -Llp 9876 | wc -l (250 threads)
5. Memory dump - jmap -dump:live,format=b,file=/tmp/heap.hprof 9876
6. Restart Tomcat - systemctl restart tomcat9
7. Verify recovery - top + CloudWatch HeapUsed dropping
8. Prevention note - "Added thread limit to Tomcat config"

SUMMARY: All Linux CPU Issues Detection Pattern
Issue Type	Jira Clue	top Shows	Root Fix
Real CPU	CPUUtil 95%	apache2 1200%	kill -9 PID
Zombies	Load 18.5, CPU 18%	127 "Z" procs	kill parent PID
I/O Wait	Disk 95%, %wa 65%	iostat %util=95%	renice + drop_caches
Java	java 450% CPU	250 threads	jmap + restart
UNIVERSAL 60-SECOND CPU CHECKLIST
bash
1. top                    # CPU% or "Z" processes?
2. ps aux --sort=-%cpu | head -5  # Real CPU hogs
3. ps aux | grep defunct | wc -l  # Zombie count
4. iostat -x 1 3          # I/O wait?
5. jps -l                  # Java processes
JIRA CLOSING PHRASES (Copy-Paste)
text
âœ… RESOLVED: [process] [PID] killed + service restarted
âœ… FIXED: [count] zombies â†’ parent PID [number] terminated
âœ… MITIGATED: I/O throttling + cache cleared, monitoring
âœ… RESTARTED: Java heap dump taken + Tomcat restarted
These 4 patterns = 90% of LotusFlare Linux CPU alerts. Your friend masters this = night shift hero. Memory issues next?
